     <div type="to_the_reader">
   <pb facs="5"/>
   <head>To the Reader.</head>
   <l>REad o're this little book, &amp; in it see,</l>
   <l>What paines the Author hath bestow'd for thee</l>
   <l>And thy delight, for t'is alone compil'd</l>
   <l>For vertues luster, and not meanely stil'd</l>
   <l>For if all Poets which this land doth yeeld,</l>
   <l>Could bring <hi>Mars</hi> armed in a bloudy field,</l>
   <l>Or paint the violence of the waters <hi>king,</hi>
   </l>
   <l>Or with blinde <hi>Cupid</hi> in his Courts thus sing,</l>
   <l>This land (as erst the <hi>Italian</hi> bounds) mighe be</l>
   <l>Fam'd for the nursing of true Poetrie.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>H. I.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
